ocrText:
Assistive Utensil Design Description  
Design Background: Left-hand dysfunction, unstable grip, prone to slipping.  
Design Objectives: Easy to grip, slip-resistant, provides assistance.  
Selected Solution: S-shaped curved spoon handle, thickened in the middle, with a slip-resistant bumpy texture on the surface.  
Preliminary Dimensions: Total length 150mm, grip diameter 25mm.  
Material Concept: Main body made of hardwood, key contact surfaces considering food-grade silicone.  
Weight Target: <50g.  
Reference: Ergonomic data from the Mechanical Design Handbook.

ocrText:
Key Points for Applying Wood Wax Oil:  
1. Environmental Requirements: Well-ventilated, dust-free, temperature between 15-25°C.  
2. Thin Coats, Multiple Layers: Allow 6-8 hours between coats, lightly sand with fine sandpaper (400 grit or higher).  
3. Sanding Technique: Sand along the wood grain with even pressure.  
4. Drying Time: Surface dry in 2-4 hours, fully dry in 24-48 hours.
